This is an accessory for the T4 quadcopter. This simple adapter plate allows a variety of "action" cameras (eg GoPro. Mobius, etc) to be mounted on the front of the T4 using vibration gel and a rubber band. Here's a sample flight video and its not too bad for a very simple and quick option.

In honor of the season finale of the walking dead, I've decided to share my neat little head remix. Simply boulean your head onto the platform and hit print. There's also a picture of me in there to show the source of the arms and my head.

Designed to demonstrate how a simple object can show a complex process. Use a piece of filament to connect the idea to the extruder head and you have a an easy way to tell folks about 3D printing. I left the extruder head open on the top, would be curious to see how it looks closed if you are so inclined. Enjoy!
This is a 3d model of the portal gun that is featured in the video games Portal and Portal 2. It was made in Cinema 4d

Tell me how printing goes! It might be difficult with the arms though
